header::Perl Datatypes
chapter::Perl Datatypes
Perl has three typedefs which handle Perl' s [[em:three main data types]].
|SV|Scalar Value
|AV|Array Value
|HV|Hash Value
----
[[#pre:Other Datatypes]]
|IV|integer variables
|UV|unsigned integer variables
|I32|32-bits integer
|U32|unsigned 32-bits integer
|I16|16-bits integer
|U16|unsigned 16-bits integer
|NV|double variables
|PV|string variables
----
SV
----
[[#kw:☼]][[#pre:SV: Create]]
[[pre:
SV* newSV();
]]
----
[[#kw:☼]][[#pre:SV: Apply]]
[[pre:
SV*  newSViv(IV);
SV*  newSVuv(UV);
SV*  newSVnv(double);
SV*  newSVpv(const char*, STRLEN);
SV*  newSVpvn(const char*, STRLEN);
SV*  newSVpvf(const char*, ...);
SV*  newSVsv(SV*);
]]
----
[[#kw:☼]][[#pre:SV: Modify]]
[[pre:
void  sv_setiv(SV*, IV);
void  sv_setuv(SV*, UV);
void  sv_setnv(SV*, double);
void  sv_setpv(SV*, const char*);
void  sv_setpvn(SV*, const char*, STRLEN);
void  sv_setpvf(SV*, const char*, ...);
void  sv_vsetpvfn(SV*, const char*, STRLEN, va_list *, SV **, I32, bool *);
void  sv_setsv(SV*, SV*);
]]
----
[[#kw:☼]][[#pre:SV: Access Actual Value]]
[[pre:
SvIV(SV*)
SvUV(SV*)
SvNV(SV*)
